title: Asian Ramen-Chicken Chopped Salad
summary: Asian Ramen-Chicken Chopped Salad might be just the main course you are searching for. Watching your figure? This dairy free recipe has 718 calories, 30g of protein, and 43g of fat per serving. For $1.92 per serving, this recipe covers 36% of your daily requirements of vitamins and minerals. This recipe from Cooking Classy has 6886 fans. From preparation to the plate, this recipe takes roughly 45 minutes. If you have onion powder, granulated sugar, ginger, and a few other ingredients on hand, you can make it. To use up the salt you could follow this main course with the Apple Turnovers Recipe as a dessert. All things considered, we decided this recipe deserves a spoonacular score of 98%. winePairing.pairingText: Ramen Noodles works really well with Riesling, Sake, and Sauvignon Blanc. Saké is an obvious choice when it comes to Japanese food. If you want to stick to grape wine, though, you might opt for sauvignon blanc or riesling. One wine you could try is J.J. Prum Bernkasteler Badstube Spatlese Riesling. It has 4.6 out of 5 stars and a bottle costs about 30 dollars.

instructions: Preheat oven to 400 degrees. Crumble ramen into small pieces and place on baking sheet along with almonds, spread into an even layer. Bake in preheated oven until golden, tossing once halfway through baking, about 6 - 8 minutes. Set aside to cool.In a mixing bowl whisk together all of the dressing ingredients until well blended while seasoning with salt to taste, set aside.To a large bowl add green cabbage, purple cabbage, carrots, green onions, chicken, toasted ramen and almonds and sesame seeds. Drizzle dressing over top and toss to evenly coat. Serve right away for crunchiest results.*If desired you can also use a 16 oz coleslaw mix in place of the cabbages and carrot, I just prefer the freshly chopped for this recipe, plus the mixes are skimpy on the purple cabbage.Recipe Source: inspired by Betty Crocker
